Spec: Distribution Applier Service
Purpose:
  Apply files from a SpecDD distribution zip into a target directory while preserving local project choices during update.

Structure:
  ./distribution-applier.ts: Distribution applier service implementation.
  ./distribution-applier.test.ts: Distribution applier tests.

Owns:
  ./distribution-applier.ts
  ./distribution-applier.test.ts

References:
  ../../infrastructure/file-system.sdd
  ../logger/service.sdd

Must:
  Accept @Logger and @FileSystem through constructor parameters.
  Accept a path to a distribution .zip file, a target directory path, and an apply mode.
  Inspect file entries inside the zip archive.
  Check target file existence through @FileSystem before writing.
  Explicitly create parent directories through @FileSystem before writing files.
  Write a missing zip file entry during init.
  During update, write a missing zip file entry only when the normalized relative path is .specdd/bootstrap.md.
  Overwrite an existing target file only when the normalized relative path is .specdd/bootstrap.md.
  Leave every other existing target file unchanged.
  During update, leave every missing non-bootstrap target file unchanged.
  Create parent directories needed for files that are written.
  Return paths for files written, files overwritten, and files skipped.
  Reject zip entries that resolve outside the target directory.

Must not:
  Delete target files or directories.
  Overwrite existing files other than .specdd/bootstrap.md.
  Recreate missing or deleted non-bootstrap files during update.
  Write files outside the target directory.
  Execute unzip or any other external command.

Depends on:
  @CliError
  @Logger
  @FileSystem
  jszip
  Node.js path handling

Exposes:
  @DistributionApplier
  @DistributionApplier.applyDistribution

Accepts:
  @DistributionApplyRequest

Returns:
  @DistributionApplyResult

Raises:
  @DistributionZipNotFoundError
  @DistributionZipReadError
  @DistributionUnsafeEntryPathError
  @DistributionTargetWriteError

Handles:
  empty target directory
  populated target directory
  missing target file
  existing .specdd/bootstrap.md target file
  existing non-bootstrap target file
  update with missing non-bootstrap target file
  nested zip file entry
  unsafe zip file entry path
